section.section:
A broker's lien established under this subtitle shall:
Subject to subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph, have priority over all liens of every kind perfected against the lien property after the issuance of an interlocutory order or the final order of the court under § 14-305 of this subtitle;
Be subordinate to a mechanics' lien established under Title 9 of this article, and perfected subsequent to the broker's lien if the mechanics' lien relates back to a date when work was performed or materials were furnished and that date is prior to the issuance of an interlocutory order or the final order of the court under § 14-305 of this subtitle;
Be subordinate to all liens perfected prior to the issuance of an interlocutory order or the final order of the court under § 14-305 of this subtitle, notwithstanding that the holder of a prior perfected lien had knowledge of the broker's unfiled commission claim at the time of perfection; and
Be subordinate to all other liens which are otherwise paramount to the broker's lien by operation of law.
